) {
  return getRandomResponse([
    "Grades are important, but they don’t define your worth. Focus on learning and growing from each experience.",
    "It’s okay to feel concerned about grades, but remember that effort and progress matter more than any number on a paper.",
    "Don’t let grades dictate your happiness. Use them as feedback to improve and move forward with confidence.",
    "Results can be stressful, but every setback is an opportunity to learn and grow stronger. Keep going—you’ve got this!",
    "Remember, grades are just one part of the bigger picture. Your skills, creativity, and determination count just as much."
  ]);
}
  // Stress or Anxiety
  else if (lowerCaseMessage.includes("stressed out") || lowerCaseMessage.includes("stress") || lowerCaseMessage.includes("feeling stressed") ||lowerCaseMessage.includes("feeling sad") || lowerCaseMessage.includes("feeling exhausted")) {
    return getRandomResponse([
      "Feeling stressed? Take a moment to breathe deeply with me. Inhale... Exhale. This can help you relax.",
      "Hey, I know it’s tough. Want to talk about what’s making you feel this way? Talking it out can help ease the tension.",
      "Stress can pile up sometimes. Maybe try a short walk or your favorite music? Physical movement can reduce stress."
    ]);
  } 
  
  else if (
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("anxious") || 
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("anxiety") || 
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("nervous") || 
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("worried")
  ) {
    return getRandomResponse([
      "Anxiety can be overwhelming. Let’s take a deep breath together: Inhale for 4 seconds, hold for 4, and exhale for 4. Repeat a few times.",
      "Feeling nervous? Try grounding yourself by focusing on your senses. For example, name 5 things you can see, 4 you can touch, 3 you can hear, 2 you can smell, and 1 you can taste.",
      "Remember, you’re stronger than your anxiety. Take it one moment at a time, and know that this feeling will pass."
    ]);
  }
  else if (
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("anxiety attack") ||
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("panic attack") ||
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("anxious") ||
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("panic")
  ) {
    return getRandomResponse([
      "Anxiety attacks can feel overwhelming. Try grounding yourself by focusing on your senses: name 5 things you see, 4 things you can touch, 3 things you hear, 2 things you smell, and 1 thing you taste.",
      "Take slow, deep breaths. Inhale for 4 seconds, hold for 4 seconds, and exhale for 4 seconds. Repeating this can help calm your body.",
      "It’s okay to feel this way. Remind yourself: this feeling will pass. You are safe, and it’s your body’s response to stress.",
      "If you’re having an anxiety attack, try to sit down, close your eyes, and breathe deeply. Focus on the sensation of your breath entering and leaving your body.",
      "Reach out to someone you trust. Talking through what you’re feeling can help you feel less alone and more grounded."
    ]);
  }
  // No Hope
else if (
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("no hope") || 
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("hopeless") || 
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("feel empty") || 
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("nothing matters")
) {
  return getRandomResponse([
    "I’m really sorry you’re feeling this way, but I want you to know that even in the darkest moments, there is always a path forward.",
    "Sometimes, life can feel overwhelming, but even small steps can lead to meaningful change. You’re not alone in this.",
    "When hope feels distant, it’s okay to take a break and focus on something small and positive. You don’t have to tackle everything at once.",
    "It’s okay to feel like this sometimes, but please reach out to someone who can support you. There is always a way to start rebuilding hope.",
    "I know it’s hard right now, but things can get better. It may take time, but there are always brighter days ahead. Hang in there."
  ]);
