      "Mindfulness is like a mini-reset. Have you tried focusing entirely on a small task, like sipping tea or feeling the texture of an object?",
      "Sometimes mindfulness is just pausing and appreciating the present moment. Can you think of one thing you're grateful for right now?",
      "Mindfulness takes practice, but even a few moments of deep breathing can help center your thoughts. Would you like to try a guided exercise?"
    ]);
  }
  // Feeling Confident
else if (
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("feeling confident") || 
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("confidence boost") || 
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("self-assurance") || 
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("believe in myself")
) {
  return getRandomResponse([
    "Confidence comes from acknowledging your strengths and understanding your potential. Start by focusing on the things you do well, and celebrate your achievements, no matter how small. It’s also important to surround yourself with positive people who uplift and encourage you to be your best self.",
    "Confidence isn’t something that happens overnight. It’s built through consistent self-belief, learning, and pushing through challenges. If you’re feeling unsure, remember that everyone starts somewhere. Take pride in your progress and keep challenging yourself to grow!",
    "Sometimes, confidence comes from stepping outside your comfort zone. Try taking on new challenges, even small ones. Each success, no matter how big or small, will reinforce your belief in your abilities. And remember, mistakes are part of the learning process—don’t let them hold you back!",
    "One way to boost confidence is through positive self-talk. Instead of focusing on negative thoughts, remind yourself of your accomplishments and strengths. You’ve come so far, and you have the potential to achieve even more. Speak kindly to yourself—it makes a big difference!",
    "If you're feeling confident, remember to embrace it and share that positive energy with others! Confidence is contagious, and when you shine, others can be inspired by your belief in yourself. Keep building on that feeling, and it will help you continue to grow and face new challenges with optimism."
  ]);
}
  //Resilience
  else if (
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("resilience") ||
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("bounce back") ||
    lowerCaseMessage.includes("handle challenges")
  ) {
    return getRandomResponse([
      "Resilience is about bouncing back from tough times. Remember, every challenge you overcome makes you stronger for the next one.",
      "Building resilience takes time. Start by focusing on what you can control, practicing gratitude, and seeking support when needed.",
      "You are capable of overcoming challenges. Reflect on past moments of strength—how did you push through difficult times before?",
      "Resilience doesn’t mean you won’t feel down; it means you keep going even when things are hard. Take one step at a time.",
      "Think of resilience as a muscle—every time you face adversity and keep going, you’re strengthening it. Be kind to yourself through the process."
    ]);
  }
  // Psychologist / Therapist
else if (
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("psychologist") ||
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("therapist") ||
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("mental health professional") ||
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("counselor") ||
  lowerCaseMessage.includes("mental support")
) {
  return getPsychologistContact();
}
// Default Response
else {
  return getRandomResponse([
    "That’s interesting! Can you tell me more? I’m here to chat and help you work through it.",
    "I’m here to chat—what’s on your mind? Let’s talk through any challenges you may be facing.",
  ]);
}
// Function to provide Psychologist contact information
function getPsychologistContact() {
  return (
    "Here are some helplines you can contact in India:\n\n" +
    "1. **Blyss Mental Health** - Call: +91 9555 89 92 92\n" +
    "2. **I Call** (Mental Health Support) - Call: 9152987821 (10 AM - 8 PM)\n" +
    "3. **Samaritans Mumbai** - Call: 91-22-2772 6771 or 91-22-2772 6773\n" +
    "4. **NIMHANS** (National Institute of Mental Health and Neurosciences) - Call: +91 80 4611 0007\n" +
    "5. **YourDOST** (Online Counseling) - www.yourdost.com (Available 24/7)\n" +
    "6. **Mental Health Support** (India Helpline) - 91-22-2772 6771\n" +
    "7. **Therapists and helplines can provide the support you need. Reach out to:\n\n- **iCall**: 9152987821\n- **Mpower 1on1**: 1800-120-820050 (Mental health support in India)\n- **AASRA**: 91-9820466726 (24/7 helpline)" +
    "\nRemember, reaching out for help is a courageous step. You don't have to go through it alone. These professionals are available to provide support."
  );
}
}

function getRandomResponse(responses) {
  return responses[Math.floor(Math.random() * responses.length)];
}

// Function to suggest exercises
function getExerciseSuggestions() {
  return getRandomResponse([
    "Here are some quick exercises you can try: \n- Take a brisk 10-minute walk to refresh your mind. \n- Try a 5-minute stretch routine to release tension. \n- Do some jumping jacks for 2 minutes to get your blood flowing and boost your mood.",
    "Physical activity can boost your mood! Try these exercises: \n- 10 pushups to get your blood circulating. \n- 15 squats to release energy. \n- A 2-minute plank hold to strengthen your core."
  ]);
}
